<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
The holotype of 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. daozhenensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="daozhenensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. daozhenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deposited in CDCP and not currently available for loan and study. This nominal species was not included by 
<bibRefCitation author="Verves, YuG" journalOrPublisher="Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 68" refId="B36" refString="Verves, YuG, 2020. An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera). Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia 1: 1 - 68" title="An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera)." volume="1" year="2020">Verves (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, probably in an oversight. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Jin, DC" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="404 - 409" refId="B40" refString="Wei, LM, 2005. Sarcophagidae. In: Jin, DC, Li, ZZ, Eds., Insects from Xishui Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 404 - 409" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Xishui Landscape." year="2005">Wei (2005)</bibRefCitation>
described the vesica as flower-like, the cerci as having pointed apices and being slightly bent in lateral view, and the juxtal extension as well developed, flexed at its base and bent forward apically (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Sarcophaga (Liosarcophaga) aegyptica Salem, 1935; male (China, Qinghai; in SECA) A habitus, lateral view B terminalia, lateral view C head, lateral view D head, anterolateral view E head, anterior view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.83267.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706069" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">4</figureCitation>
). All of these features are consistent with 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. sichotealini" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="sichotealini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">S. sichotealini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we consider the illustrations of the phallus provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, Wq" journalOrPublisher="Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B44" refString="Xue, Wq, Chao, Cm, 1998. Flies of China. Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" title="Flies of China." year="1998">Xue and Chao (1998</bibRefCitation>
: 677, fig. 1332 m), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Yang, MF" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Peoples Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="422 - 427" refId="B41" refString="Wei, LM, Yang, ZH, 2005. Diptera: Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae, Muscidae, Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae. In: Yang, MF, Jin, DC, Eds., Insects from Dashahe Nature Reserve of Guizhou. Guizhou Peoples Publishing House, Guiyang: 422 - 427" title="Diptera: Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae, Muscidae, Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Dashahe Nature Reserve of Guizhou." year="2005">Wei and Yang (2005</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3) to be a fully acceptable match (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Sarcophaga (Phallantha) sichotealini Rohdendorf, 1938; phallus, lateral view A illustrated from figure 7 B B adapted from Wei and Yang (2005, as Pierretia daozhenensis)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.83267.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706073" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">8</figureCitation>
). We notice that 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Yang, MF" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Peoples Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="422 - 427" refId="B41" refString="Wei, LM, Yang, ZH, 2005. Diptera: Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae, Muscidae, Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae. In: Yang, MF, Jin, DC, Eds., Insects from Dashahe Nature Reserve of Guizhou. Guizhou Peoples Publishing House, Guiyang: 422 - 427" title="Diptera: Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae, Muscidae, Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Dashahe Nature Reserve of Guizhou." year="2005">Wei and Yang (2005)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. daozhenensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="daozhenensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. daozhenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was assigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pierretia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pierretia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pierretia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using the key by 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, Wq" journalOrPublisher="Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B44" refString="Xue, Wq, Chao, Cm, 1998. Flies of China. Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" title="Flies of China." year="1998">Xue and Chao (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, but the species was not assigned to any of the subgenera applied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, Wq" journalOrPublisher="Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B44" refString="Xue, Wq, Chao, Cm, 1998. Flies of China. Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" title="Flies of China." year="1998">Xue and Chao (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, which includes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Phallantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phallantha" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Phallantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Yang, MF" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Peoples Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="422 - 427" refId="B41" refString="Wei, LM, Yang, ZH, 2005. Diptera: Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae, Muscidae, Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae. In: Yang, MF, Jin, DC, Eds., Insects from Dashahe Nature Reserve of Guizhou. Guizhou Peoples Publishing House, Guiyang: 422 - 427" title="Diptera: Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae, Muscidae, Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Dashahe Nature Reserve of Guizhou." year="2005">Wei and Yang (2005)</bibRefCitation>
made no discussion about the subgeneric affiliation of 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. daozhenensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="daozhenensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. daozhenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and there is no comparison with 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. sichotealini" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="sichotealini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. sichotealini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in spite of the significant similarities with the illustration provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, Wq" journalOrPublisher="Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B44" refString="Xue, Wq, Chao, Cm, 1998. Flies of China. Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" title="Flies of China." year="1998">Xue and Chao (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. Vesica and harpes are of the same overall configuration, and as these are composed of flattened, partly membranous structures, even small changes in orientation may result in considerable changes in outline. The juxta has a very characteristic shape, with an almost exact match. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rohdendorf" baseAuthorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga (P.) sichotealini" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichotealini" subGenus="P.">Sarcophaga (P.) sichotealini</taxonomicName>
is distributed in China (Guizhou, Hunan, Sichuan, Yunnan), the Russian Far East, South Korea, and temperate Japan (
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T" journalOrPublisher="International" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 558" refId="B22" refString="Pape, T, 1996. Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology. International 8: 1 - 558" title="Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology." volume="8" year="1996">Pape 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, Wq" journalOrPublisher="Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B44" refString="Xue, Wq, Chao, Cm, 1998. Flies of China. Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" title="Flies of China." year="1998">Xue and Chao 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Verves, YuG" journalOrPublisher="Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 68" refId="B36" refString="Verves, YuG, 2020. An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera). Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia 1: 1 - 68" title="An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera)." volume="1" year="2020">Verves 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
